{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3527955,"name":"Aidan Anderson","username":"Spectre","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/e99b99/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-15T16:32:39.132Z","cooked":"<p>I believe we correctly configured the AutoBuilder, but when we run our path the DriveRobot relative method only gets called once, making our robot drive forward indefinitely. It seems like it’s getting hung up on something else but we’re not sure what because nothing else happens in our code during the auto period besides this. If anyone’s had a similar problem any help would be appreciated.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">AutoBuilder.configure(
    this::getPose2d,
    this::resetOdometry,
    this::getRobotRelativeSpeeds,
    (speeds, feedforwards)-&gt;{
      //System.out.println("Hello");
      driveRobotRelative(speeds);
    },
    new PPHolonomicDriveController(new com.pathplanner.lib.config.PIDConstants(0.1, 0, 0), new com.pathplanner.lib.config.PIDConstants(0.1, 0, 0)),
    config,
    () -&gt; {
                // Boolean supplier that controls when the path will be mirrored for the red alliance
                // This will flip the path being followed to the red side of the field.
                 // THE ORIGIN WILL REMAIN ON THE BLUE SIDE

        var alliance = DriverStation.getAlliance();
        if (alliance.isPresent()) {
            return alliance.get() == DriverStation.Alliance.Red;
        }
        return false;
    },
    this
    );
</code></pre>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":2,"updated_at":"2025-02-15T16:32:39.132Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":13,"reads":25,"readers_count":24,"score":70.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":491809,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-only-calling-driverobotrelative-once","display_username":"Aidan Anderson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":64679,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Coder"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-only-calling-driverobotrelative-once/491809/1","custom_user_title":"Coder","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3527958,"name":"Aidan Anderson","username":"Spectre","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/e99b99/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-15T16:34:28.682Z","cooked":"<p>Our getAutonomous method. We’ve tried both:</p>
